00020161 - 咬合學 Occlusion, Fall  2009











Occlusion
咬合學
吳慶榕 Professor X, Ph.D.
周孫隆 Professor X, Ph.D
College of Oral Medicine
            Taipei Medical University
Course Structure: 2 Hours per week




Image courtesy of eduCommons (275px x 275px)
Course Description
This course introduce the concept of occlusion to the dental student from basic mastictory anatomy and physiology, articulator and its application and ideal occlusion and occlusal adjustment.
咬合理論的介紹，咬合解剖、生理,咬合器介紹，理想咬合及調整等使學生對咬合學有一初步認識．





